<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="446" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1112,1551]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
resurrected as 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,848,1320,1343]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">valid species</emphasis>
from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Fischer von Waldheim, 1821" authorityName="Fischer von Waldheim" authorityYear="1821" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Brachyrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1350,1320,1343]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Brachyrhinus granulatus</emphasis>
Fischer von Waldheim, 1821
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[380,475,1354,1377]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">stat. res.</emphasis>
(LT of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[556,708,1354,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Maximus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosus">
<emphasis box="[556,708,1354,1377]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">M. verrucosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
examined, photograph in WCC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="446" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1112,1551]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,303,1389,1412]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fahraeus, 1842)" authorityName="Fahraeus" authorityYear="1842" baseAuthorityName="Fahraeus" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[316,741,1389,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Chromosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fischeri">
<emphasis box="[316,555,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Chromosomus fischeri</emphasis>
(FÃ¥hraeus, 1842)
</taxonomicName>
is a name currently used for a well-known species widespread in central Asia. However, it has a senior synonym, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fischer von Waldheim, 1821" authorityName="Fischer von Waldheim" authorityYear="1821" box="[675,1264,1424,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Brachyrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis box="[675,943,1424,1447]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Brachyrhinus granulatus</emphasis>
Fischer von Waldheim, 1821
</taxonomicName>
. The synonymy between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer von Waldheim" authorityYear="1821" box="[247,393,1458,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Brachyrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis box="[247,393,1458,1481]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">B. granulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fahraeus" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[447,559,1458,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Chromosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fischeri">
<emphasis box="[447,559,1458,1481]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">C. fischeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been generally recognized, at least since 
<bibRefCitation author="Faust" box="[1051,1241,1458,1481]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Faust, J. (1904) Revision der Gruppe Cleonides vrais. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1904 (1), 177 - 284. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 48019040120" type="journal article" year="1904">Faust (1904: 208)</bibRefCitation>
but, for unknown reasons, the correct priority was never adopted. In 
<collectionCode box="[689,739,1493,1516]" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3snx-0r7t" name="Culture collection of Pedro Crous" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">CPC</collectionCode>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer von Waldheim" authorityYear="1821" box="[746,890,1493,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Brachyrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis box="[746,890,1493,1516]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">B. granulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erroneously referred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alonso-Zarazaga &amp; Lyal" authorityYear="2009" box="[1303,1401,1493,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Maximus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1303,1401,1493,1516]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Maximus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[395,547,1528,1551]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Maximus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosus">
<emphasis box="[395,547,1528,1551]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">M. verrucosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
